{"word":"H7194 - קָשַׁר - qâshar - kaw-shar' - Bind","slug":"H7194","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">קָשַׁר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>qâshar"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kaw-shar'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Bind"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E7;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05E8; - qa&#x0302;shar</b> - <i>kaw-shar'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>tie</i>, physically (<i>gird</i>, <i>confine</i>, <i>compact</i>) or mentally (in <i>love</i>, <i>league</i>): - bind (up), (make a) conspire (-acy, -ator), join together, knit, stronger, work [treason]."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H7195\">H7195</a>, <a href=\"#/H7196\">H7196</a>"}]}